<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 7:42PM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of northwestern Union
and central Columbia Counties through 830 PM CDT...
At 741 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Calion to Smithland. Movement was
southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
El Dorado, Magnolia, Smackover, Norphlet, Calion, Village, Lisbon,
Mount Holly, Smithland, Macedonia, Calhoun, Ebenezer, Laughlin,
Pigeon Hill, Marysville, Cairo, Noxobe, Kenova and Spotville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
